title: Easy Tandoori Chicken Masala Recipe, Smoky, Rich & Creamy Chicken Recipe by Samina Food Story
description:
Craving that iconic, smoky flavor of restaurant-style tandoori chicken masala? In this video, I’ll show you how to make an *authentic, incredibly flavorful Smoky Tandoori Chicken Masala at home* using simple methods—no clay tandoor oven required! We’ll create a vibrant yogurt marinade, cook juicy chicken, and build a rich, creamy masala gravy, all packed with those charred, aromatic spices and that signature smoky taste.

🔴 In This Video, You’ll Learn:
✅ The secret to the perfect yogurt-based tandoori marinade.
✅ 3 different techniques to get that authentic smoky flavor (using charcoal, wood chips, or a simple kitchen hack!).
✅ How to cook the chicken perfectly—juicy on the inside, charred on the outside.
✅ Building a creamy, restaurant-style masala gravy from scratch.
✅ My pro tips for saving time and maximizing flavor.

📝 INGREDIENTS & RECIPE (Key Highlights):

*For the best Paste:*    
• Garlic cloves: 4-5
• Ginger: 3-4
• Dry red chili: 8-10
• Fresh coriander        
► *Add water a little at a time while blending, until it forms a paste.*    
       
*For the Tandoori Marinade:*    
• Chicken drumsticks: 600 gram        
• Add blended paste!        
• Yogurt/dahi: 1 cup        
• Red chili powder: 1 tsp        
• Salt: 1 & 1/2 tsp          
• Coriander powder: 1 tbsp        
• Black pepper powder: 1 tsp        
• Turmeric/haldi  powder: 1/2 tsp        
• Tandoori Masala: 1 tsp    
        
*For the Frying Chicken:*    
• Oil: 1 tbsp 
► *Cook chicken on medium flame*    
   
*Finalizing:*        
• Oil: 3-4 tbsp        
► *Cook on one side for 2-3 minutes over medium heat, then turn.*        
► *Again cook other side for 2-3 minutes over medium heat, then turn.*        
• Onion chopped: 1 large size        
• Ginger garlic paste: 1 tbsp        
► *Now add yogurt spice mixture.!*              
► *Add fried chicken pieces.!*        
• Water:  1 cup         
► *Cover it & cook it for 8-10 min on medium low flame!*        
• Fresh cream: 2 tbsp         
► *Now, place a piece of aluminum foil or a metal plate.!*        
► *Next, take the burnt coil & set it on the foil or plate.*
► *Carefully place one drop of oil on top of it.*    
► *Now cover it for 2 min on low flame!*        
► *Fresh coriander(chopped).!* 

👨🍳*SERVING SUGGESTIONS:*
This smoky tandoori chicken masala pairs perfectly with:
• Butter Naan or Garlic Naan
• Basmati Rice or Jeera Rice
• A side of onion salad (pyaz ka laccha) and mint chutney.

title: Old Style Mutton Stew Recipe | Amma's Special Mutton Recipe | Food With Saad Raja
description:
Old Style Mutton Stew Recipe | Amma's Special Mutton Recipe | Food With Saad Raja

Recipe and Ingredients
In a pan add 200g ghee and add 2 medium sliced onions and cook for a minute. Now add 1 kg mutton, 2 tbsp crushed ginger, 2 tbsp crushed garlic, 2 tbsp crushed coriander,  1 tsp cumin powder, 1-1/2 tsp salt, 8-10 red whole chilies, 1/2 tsp turmeric, 2 staranise, 2 black cardamom, 2 cinnamon sticks, 1 tbsp coriander crushed and 5-7 cloves. Cook for 2 minutes and add 3 cups pf water and cook on pressure for 15 minutes. 

Now let it cook for 5 minutes so that remaining water evaporates. Then add 250g tomatos and 250g yogurt and let it cook for 8-10 minutes. Once cooked add 1 tsp garam masala, some fresh coriander and mutton stew is ready to be served!

title: The Cheapest Breakfast You Can Make | Steel Cut Oats Recipe
description:
If you’re looking for a cheap, healthy breakfast that saves both time and money, this video shows how I make steel cut oats in a simple way that lasts for several days. Steel cut oats are one of the most affordable breakfasts you can make, especially when you buy them in bulk, and they’re a powerful way to reduce your grocery bill while still eating well.

In this video, I show how I make a basic batch using 1 cup of steel cut oats and 1¾ cups of water, which creates enough oatmeal for multiple servings without standing at the stove every morning. One cup of cooked oatmeal makes 4 servings, and you can store it in the refrigerator to reheat throughout the week, perfect for busy mornings and simple meal prep.

Buying steel cut oats in bulk and storing them in a gallon glass jar keeps them fresh and incredibly affordable, about 5 cents per serving. Choosing this breakfast regularly can save hundreds of dollars a year compared to packaged or convenience breakfasts, making it one of the best budget staples you can keep on hand.

I also share how I boost the nutrition by adding affordable pantry staples:
• Chia seeds for fiber and about 4g of protein
• Hemp hearts (2 tablespoons = 7g protein)
• Ground flaxseed for healthy fats, fiber, and 3g protein

All of these add-ins can be stored in glass jars so they stay fresh and ready to use. You can also add fresh produce like apples, bananas, or blueberries to naturally sweeten your oatmeal and add flavor without added sugar.

If you want a budget-friendly breakfast, easy meal prep ideas, or a simple way to save money on groceries while eating nourishing food, steel cut oats are one of the best habits you can start.

title: Chimichurri Beef Undercut | Restaurant-Style Recipe | Shireen Anwar | Masala TV
description:
Subscribe to Masala TV Recipes here: https://bit.ly/MasalaTV

Indulge in a restaurant-style Chimichurri Beef Undercut with Shireen Anwar on @MasalaTVRecipes 
This tender beef cut is perfectly cooked and coated with a vibrant chimichurri sauce, combining fresh herbs, garlic, and olive oil for a bold, zesty flavor that elevates your dining experience at home.

Perfect for dinner parties, weekend feasts, or special occasions, this dish pairs beautifully with roasted vegetables, garlic bread, or creamy mashed potatoes.

👇 RECIPE CARD 
Chimichurri Beef Under Cut
 
Beef Under Cut (1 portion)
Ingredient 
Beef under cut  220 grams
Salt    3 grams
Crushed black pepper 3 grams
Olive oil   10 ml
Garlic (whole)  2 pieces
Fresh thyme   2 pieces
Butter    25 grams
Chimichurri Sauce Ingredients:
Coriander   100 grams
Parsley   100 grams
Jalapeno (chopped) 50 grams
Salt    5 grams
Black pepper  5 grams
Crushed red chili  5 grams
Whole grain mustard 25 grams
Garlic (chopped)  25 grams
Olive oil   150 grams
Red wine vinegar  15 grams
Lemon juice   15 grams
Method
For the Chimichurri sauce, finely chop coriander, parsley, jalapeno, garlic, salt, black pepper, crushed red chili, and whole grain mustard. Add red wine vinegar and lemon juice. Finally add olive oil and mix gently. Do not make the sauce into a paste.
For the beef under cut, pat the beef dry with a kitchen towel. Season both sides with salt and crushed black pepper. Lightly rub olive oil on top and keep at room temperature for 10–15 minutes. Heat a cast iron or heavy pan on high heat. Add a little oil and place the beef under cut in the pan. Cook each side for 2½ to 3 minutes without moving until well browned. Add butter, whole garlic, and fresh thyme to the pan. Spoon the melted butter over the beef repeatedly. Remove the beef from the pan and let it rest for 3–4 minutes. Slice the beef under cut and serve with Chimichurri sauce on top or on the side.

title: Moist Mexican Cornbread in a Cast Iron Skillet | Easy Southern Recipe
description:
This Mexican Cornbread is golden, cheesy, and baked to perfection in a cast iron skillet. Loaded with corn, cheese, and just the right amount of kick, this easy Southern-style recipe is moist on the inside with a crispy crust on the outside.
Perfect as a side dish for chili, soups, BBQ, or your favorite comfort food meals. This is a family-style Mexican cornbread recipe that never lasts long on the table! This Mexican cornbread is cheesy, moist, and packed with flavor—perfect for cast iron cooking and Southern comfort meals.
👉 If you love Southern cooking, cast iron recipes, and old-fashioned comfort food, you’re in the right place.
Ingredients & full recipe in the description — don’t forget to like, subscribe, and comment!

🧀🌽 Mexican Cornbread Ingredients
2 ½ cups cornmeal mix
1 medium white onion, diced
1 red or green bell pepper, diced
1 jalapeño, finely chopped
(Add extra jalapeño if you like it hot)
1 pinch cayenne pepper
Black pepper, to taste
2 large eggs
⅔ cup canola oil or vegetable oil
½ cup buttermilk
1 (15 oz) can creamed-style corn
1 block Colby or Cheddar cheese, freshly grated

🥘 Mexican Cornbread Directions (Cast Iron)
Preheat the oven to 375°F.
Place a cast iron skillet in the oven with 2/3 cup of oil in skillet. Let the oil get hot while the oven preheats.
Sauté the vegetables.
In a skillet, sauté the diced onion and bell pepper until softened. Remove from heat.

Mix the batter.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except the cheese.
Carefully pour the hot oil from the skillet into the batter and stir well.

Layer the cornbread.
Pour half of the batter into the hot cast iron skillet.
Add jalapenos, onions and bell peppers to the remaining mix.
Add half of the cheese.

Finish and top.
Pour the remaining batter into the skillet, then sprinkle with the remaining cheese.

Bake.
Bake at 375°F for 25–35 minutes, or until golden brown and a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

Rest and serve.
Let cool slightly before slicing. Serve warm.
